If you notice the current RoleDTO, it is throwing IllegalArgumentExceptions in case during setUsers or setPermissions, in case any of the elements within those collections are null. Now that we don't have control over the setters, we can't do that, so we need another way to validate the collections. This is where the DTOValidator class comes in (it was introduced in my ActivationKeyDTO PR).
Before translating here, you should add a call to the DTOValidator to check those two collections as such:
validator.validateCollectionElementsNotNull(dto::getUsers, update::getPermissions);

